  "text": "GCC's RTL (Register Transfer Language) pass chain is hierarchically organized with the following key components:\n\n**Base Pass Architecture (gcc/tree-pass.h):**\nThe RTL pass system is built on the `opt_pass` base class (line 73), which defines the core interface for all optimization passes. The `rtl_opt_pass` class (lines 125-133) is a derived class specifically for RTL passes, inheriting from `opt_pass`. This architecture also includes `gimple_opt_pass` for GIMPLE-level passes, allowing GCC to cleanly separate different intermediate representations.\n\n**Pass Expansion (Gimple to RTL - gcc/cfgexpand.cc):**\nThe `pass_expand` class (lines 7010-7020) implements the critical transformation from GIMPLE intermediate representation to RTL. This pass is instantiated via `make_pass_expand()` (line 7509). The cfgexpand.cc file is explicitly documented as \"A pass for lowering trees to RTL\" (line 1), converting high-level control flow graphs into register transfer language suitable for hardware-level optimization.\n\n**RTL Optimization Pass Example (gcc/combine.cc):**\nThe `pass_combine` class (lines 15268-15283) represents a typical RTL optimization pass, implementing instruction combining to reduce the number of instructions. It derives from `rtl_opt_pass` and is instantiated via `make_pass_combine()` (line 15288). This pass demonstrates the pattern used by RTL optimizations: gating on optimization levels, executing domain-specific optimization code, and managing dataflow information cleanup.\n\n**Code Generation Pass (gcc/final.cc):**\nThe `pass_final` class (lines 4340-4353) is the final code generation pass that converts RTL into machine code. Instantiated via `make_pass_final()` (line 4358), it calls `rest_of_handle_final()` to generate assembly output. This pass operates at the end of the RTL pass pipeline, after register allocation and instruction scheduling.\n\n**Pass Chain Organization (gcc/passes.def):**\nThe overall pass sequence is defined in passes.def. The RTL portion of the pass chain begins with `pass_expand` (line 460) and continues through `pass_rest_of_compilation` (line 462), which contains the nested RTL optimization passes. Key RTL passes in order include: pass_instantiate_virtual_regs (line 464), pass_jump (line 466), pass_cse (line 469), pass_combine (line 501), pass_ira for register allocation (line 519), pass_reload (line 520), and finally pass_final (line 572) within the pass_late_compilation group.\n\n**Pass Manager Infrastructure (gcc/pass_manager.h and gcc/passes.cc):**\nThe `pass_manager` class (pass_manager.h, line 47) orchestrates the entire compilation pipeline, maintaining references to all pass instances through auto-generated fields. The gcc/passes.cc file implements the execution logic for passes, including `execute_one_pass()` and `execute_pass_list()` functions that traverse and execute the pass chain.\n\nThis architecture cleanly separates concerns: tree-pass.h defines the interface, passes.def specifies the execution order, individual pass files (cfgexpand.cc, combine.cc, final.cc, etc.) implement specific transformations, and the pass_manager coordinates the entire pipeline. The rtl_opt_pass class serves as the unifying abstraction for all RTL-level transformations, allowing GCC to apply diverse optimization techniques within a consistent framework."
}

